reviewText:
Gene Autry and Roy Rogers ride the range in this impressive set of 27 feature films.  If you're just starting your collection, you can't go wrong with this collection of films from the silver screen's most-prolific singing cowboys.  For those Westerns fans that have a fairly extensive collection, though, there are few films that haven't been distributed widely in other budget compilations.  In fact, this set is merely a repackaging of other Platinum Disc offerings under their TV Classic Westerns and The Great American Western collections.  Another caveat is that many of the films have been edited from their original length to fit in an hour TV time slot.  Although there's been no attempt to remaster the films, all are copied from prints that range from decent to very good quality.  Films included in this set are:

Man from Music Mountain (1938) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Carol Hughes, Sally Payne, Ivan Miller (53 minutes / originally 59 min)
Oh, Susanna! (1936) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Frances Grant, Earle Hodgins (54 minutes / originally 59 min.)
The Old Barn Dance (1938) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Joan Valerie (53 minutes / originally 60 min.)
The Old Corral (1936) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Irene Manning (as Hope Manning) (53 minutes / originally 57 min.)
Public Cowboy No. 1 (1937) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Ann Rutherford, Arthur Loft (53 minutes / originally 61 min.)
Ride, Ranger, Ride (1936) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Kay Hughes, Monte Blue (51 minutes / originally 63 min.)
Rim of the Canyon (1949) - Gene Autry, Nan Leslie, Thurston Hall (69 minutes)
Yodelin' Kid from Pine Ridge (1937) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Betty Bronson, LeRoy Mason, Charles Middleton  (53 minutes / originally 60 min.)
Riders of the Whistling Pines (1949) - Gene Autry, Patricia Barry (as Patricia White), Jimmy Lloyd, Douglas Dumbrille (69 minutes)
The Big Show (1937) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Kay Hughes, Sally Payne (53 minutes / originally 71 min.)
Springtime in the Rockies (1937) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Polly Rowles, Ula Love (54 minutes / originally 60 min.)
Boots and Saddles (1937) - Gene Autry, Smiley Burnette, Judith Allen (53 minutes / originally 58 min.)

King of the Cowboys (1943) - Roy Rogers, Smiley Burnette, Peggy Moran, Gerald Mohr, Dorothea Kent (73 minutes)
My Pal Trigger (1946) - Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, Jack Holt, LeRoy Mason (79 minutes)
Song of Texas (1943) - Roy Rogers, Sheila Ryan, Barton MacLane (53 minutes / originally 69 min.)
Under California Stars (1948) - Roy Rogers, Jane Frazee, Andy Devine, George Lloyd (72 minutes)
Utah (1945) - Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, Peggy Stewart (53 minutes / originally 77 min.)
Heldorado (1946) - Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, Brad Dexter (70 minutes)
Roll On Texas Moon (1946) - Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, Dennis Hoey, Francis McDonald (66 minutes)
Under Nevada Skies (1946) - Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, Douglas Dumbrille (69 minutes)
West of the Badlands (aka The Border Legion) (1940) - Roy Rogers, Gabby Hayes, Carol Hughes, Joe Sawyer (53 minutes / originally 58 min.)
Young Bill Hickok (1940) - Roy Rogers, Gabby Hayes, Julie Bishop (as Jacqueline Wells), John Miljan, Sally Payne (53 minutes / originally 59 min.)
Hands Across the Border (1944) - Roy Rogers, Ruth Terry, Guinn `Big Boy' Williams, Onslow Stevens (54 minutes / originally 72 min.)
Billy the Kid Returns (1938) - Roy Rogers, Smiley Burnette, Lynne Roberts (as Mary Hart) (53 minutes)
Eyes of Texas (1947) - Roy Rogers, Lynne Roberts, Andy Devine, Roy Barcroft (70 minutes)
Bells of Rosarita (1945) - Roy Rogers, Dale Evans, Gabby Hayes, Grant Withers (68 minutes)
Grand Canyon Trail (1948) - Roy Rogers, Jane Frazee, Andy Devine, Robert Livingston, Roy Barcroft (66 minutes)
